  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\nHaving all the configuration parameters stored in an easily editable format (such as YAML file) enables the users to quickly edit their flags without needing to reload the systemd daemon. \r\n\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\nInstead of having \r\n```\r\nerigon \\\r\n--chain sepolia \\\r\n--port 30302 \\\r\n--datadir /root/sepolia-erigon \\\r\n--http.port 8542 \\\r\n--engine.port 8552 \r\n``` \r\none could have `erigon --config-file /path/erigon-config.yaml`\r\n\r\nWhere the config file contains:\r\n```yaml\r\nchain: \"sepolia\"\r\nport: 30302\r\ndatadir: \"/root/sepolia-erigon\"\r\nhttp.port: 8542\r\nengine.port: 8552\r\n```\r\nThe more flags you have the more benefit you'll see.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nPrysm (similarly written in go) handles the config-file flag as such:\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/cc1ea81d4a6032809cfc9d6a543d87f8392b4c74/cmd/flags.go#L266\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature? \r\nNo. Someone with more in depth knowledge of the project should implement this feature. ",
